The paper discusses training neural networks to play video games, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of information from the screen suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of different network architectures and sizes suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE) and game theory (cs.GT).
